    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jp.00209_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">N.Y.</name>
                    <date when="1891-10-30">Oct 30, 1891.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Mr. Whitman.</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Admiring you so much, my cousin<ptr target="n5001"/> and I have ventured to write and ask whether you will
                be kind enough to send us your autograph.</p>
            <p>Hoping you will not refuse to send us two autographs as we have separate
                collections,</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>I remain</salute>
                <signed>very sincerely <gap reason="cut away" quantity="4" unit="chars"/></signed>
                <signed><gap reason="illegible" quantity="5" unit="chars"/>H. <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">L.</unclear></signed>
                <signed>(Ida Strauss)</signed>
            </closer>
